    "Each individual interacts with the other agents of the population and eventually also with opinion leaders [4].",
    "Opinion leaders are characterized only by their opinion since we assume that it is always possible to interact with them.Let us start by modeling the agent-agent interactions.",
    "Let us consider an agent characterized by a level of activity and an opinion defined by the couple (A, w).",
    "When they interact with another agent having activity level and opinion (B, v), the probability that their opinion varies due to compromise dynamics depends on the respective levels of activity A and B.",
